      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_74c2dfe6cab5485fb9e46b7157ccc7ab\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fastsoftwares.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"Fixing WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR: Expert Solutions\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-05-06\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to navigation Skip to content\\n\\n#### Browse\\n\\n* [My Account](https://www.fastsoftwares.com//my-account/)\\n* [Customer Help](https://www.fastsoftwares.com/help-center-3/)\\n\\n#### Got questions?\\n\\n[Email us: [email protected]](#)\\n\\n[Home](https://www.fastsoftwares.com) / [Blog](https://www.fastsoftwares.com/category/blog/) / Fixing WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR: Expert Solutions\\n\\n# **How Do I Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?**\\n\\nfastsoftwares how to fix whea uncorrectable error 01\\n\\nWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, also known as a “blue screen of death” (BSOD), is a serious error that occurs on Windows computers, indicating that a hardware problem has occurred and the system has been shut down to prevent further damage. If you’re dealing with this error, it can be a frustrating experience, and you may feel like giving up on your computer. But don’t despair!\\n\\nYou can solve the issue and get your computer operating again by following a few simple steps.\\nTo get you back to your work or leisure activities as soon as possible, we will show you the best options to fix the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR in this guide. To resolve this issue, we will go over all the necessary details.\\n\\nIf you want to put an end to the frustration caused by this error, keep reading!\\n\\n## **What Is the WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nThis error, also known as stop code WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR or Windows code 0x0000124, is a hardware error. It indicates an issue with your computer’s hardware, such as your GPU, CPU, or RAM. The WHEA Uncorrectable Error message is also caused by voltage issues.\\n\\nThe most common causes for WHEA Uncorrectable Error are:\\n\\n* Malfunctioning hardware\\n* Driver compatibility problems\\n* Overclocking and overheating\\n* Corrupt system files or registry keys\\n* Voltage changes and issues\\n\\nBecause this error is hard to diagnose accurately, we recommend that you take a look at the automatically generated error dump file (.\\nDMP) found in C:/Windows/Minidump. Look for a file named after the date on which the error occurred and look for any details regarding what caused it. This will help you pinpoint the issue and make it easier to find a solution.\\n\\n## **How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error**\\n\\nYou can begin correcting the mistake once you have determined its source. Several options exist for resolving the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR message, depending on its origin:\\n\\n### **1] Run the CHKDSK Command**\\n\\nOne reliable method for checking for and fixing hard disk issues is to run the CHKDSK command. Run this command to check your disk for faults and see if it can fix them. Here are the steps to run CHKDSK:\\n\\n1. Press the magnifying glass icon located on your taskbar to open the search box. The **Windows key plus the S** keyboard shortcut also gives you access to it.\\n   \\n    + fastsoftwares how to fix whea uncorrectable error 02\\n2. Fill out the search field using **Command Prompt** .\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.windowsdigitals.com/whea-uncorrectable-error-windows-10-11/\",\n      \"title\": \"Windows 11/10 “Whea_Uncorrectable_Error” BSOD\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-04-23\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Windows 11/10 “Whea\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error” BSOD\\n\\nPublished by [**Nyau Wai Hoe**](https://www.windowsdigitals.com/about/) \\\\- Updated on April 23, 2024\\n\\nIf you were installing Windows 10/11, applying a Windows Update, or using your computer normally, you may have received a Blue screen of death with a STOP error that reads **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** . This error occurs when Windows detects a hardware error while running the operating system, which could be caused by hardware failure or incorrect or faulty drivers.\\n\\nIn this post, we will discuss what the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR Blue Screen of Death error means, and provide you with various methods to fix it in Windows 11 or Windows 10.\\n\\nWhea Uncorrectable Error Windows 10\\n\\n## What is Whea\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error?\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR blue screen error can occur randomly, forcing your computer to shut down to protect your data. The error occurs when Windows detects a hardware error while running the OS.\\nThis error message may indicate a hardware failure or incorrect/faulty drivers.\\n\\n## What causes the Whea\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error?\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR STOP code error usually indicates a hardware error, which can be due to various reasons such as:\\n\\n* Incorrectly overclocked hardware\\n* Hardware failure such as damaged RAM, processor or graphics card\\n* Incorrect or faulty drivers\\n* Driver issue after a Windows update\\n\\n## How to fix Whea\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error BSOD\\n\\nBelow are some methods to fix the BSOD error on your Windows 11 or 10 computer:\\n\\n### Stop Overclocking Your Hardware\\n\\nIf you have previously overclocked any hardware, you should temporarily disable the overclock settings and set your hardware’s clock speed back to its default value. Depending on how you overclocked your processor, RAM or graphics card, you may need to restore the default clock value via BIOS settings or simply by turning off or uninstalling the overclocking software.\\nDisable overclock WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\\n\\nThe screenshot above is an example of the clock speed setting in a specific BIOS interface. If it’s set to “Auto,” it means that no overclocking has been applied. If it’s set to anything else, you may be overclocking your processor.\\n\\n### Run Windows Update\\n\\nIf you’re getting the blue screen randomly after installing Windows, run [Windows Update](https://www.windowsdigitals.com/how-to-restart-windows-update-service-on-windows-11/) to receive the latest bug fixes and most importantly to update your drivers with the latest driver from Windows repository.\\n\\nTo run Windows Update in Windows 11/10, go to the start menu, type “Windows Update” and open it. Click “check for updates” to begin updating your Windows.\\n\\n### Manually update your hardware drivers\\n\\nIf you receive the error only after a Windows update, a driver installed by Windows Update could be causing conflicts between the OS and the driver.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thewindowsclub.com/whea_uncorrectable_error-0x00000124\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR 0x00000124 BSOD [Fix]\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-04-21\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[TheWindowsClub Logo](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/)\\n\\nThe Windows Club\\n\\nTheWindowsClub covers authentic Windows 11, Windows 10 tips, tutorials, how-to's, features, freeware. Created by Anand Khanse, MVP.\\n\\nShow Search\\n\\nHide Search\\n\\n# WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, 0x00000124 Blue Screen on Windows 11/10\\n\\n**[Download Windows Speedup Tool to fix errors and make PC run faster](https://reviews.thewindowsclub.com/recommends/fortectbfp/)**\\n\\nOne commonly faced Blue Screen error is **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** , **The system encountered an uncorrectable hardware** error, Code **0x00000124** . Based on the error data that is provided by the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA), this bug check indicates that a fatal hardware error has occurred. It could be caused due to the RAM, Hard Drive, or any other hardware component. It is typically related to physical hardware failures. It can be heat-related, defective hardware, memory, or even a processor that is beginning to fail or has failed.\\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR, 0x00000124 Blue Screen on Windows 11/10\\n\\n## WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR 0x00000124 BSOD\\n\\nIf you receive this error, it means that a hardware error has occurred and that your PC has shut down suddenly to protect itself from data loss. The following potential fixes can be carried out to fix BSOD errors related to _WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR_ on Windows 11/10-\\n\\n1. Disable Overclocking if you have enabled it\\n2. Ensure that your computer’s cooling systems are working\\n3. Run Diagnostics to check the Memory\\n4. Update or Rollback Drivers.\\n5. Using System File Checker.\\n6. Disable Digital Driver Signature Enforcement.\\n\\nIf you tend to create a System Restore point usually, you can try to undo any modifications on your computer by [performing System Restore](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/create-system-restore-point) . Secondly, it is recommended that you carry out these tasks mentioned below in [Safe Mode with Networking](https://www.thewindowsclub.\\ncom/boot-windows-10-in-safe-mode) only.\\n\\n#### 1] Disable Overclocking if you have enabled it\\n\\nIf [Overclocking](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/is-pc-overclocking-really-worth-it) has been enabled, try disabling it. This should help.\\n\\n#### 2] Ensure that your computer’s cooling systems are working\\n\\nYou need to get your hardware opened and check if the computer’s cooling systems like fans, etc., are working normally.\\n\\n#### 3] Run system diagnostics\\n\\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR, 0x00000124 Blue Screen on Windows 11/10\\n\\nRun [Windows Memory Diagnostics Tool](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/windows-memory-diagnostics-tool-in-windows-7) to confirm that the system memory is not defective.\\n\\n#### 4] Update or Rollback Driver\\n\\nIt is less likely, but possible, that a driver is causing the hardware to fail. So, if you recently updated a driver, roll back. If you use an old device driver, see if updates are available.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://thetechylife.com/what-causes-whea_uncorrectable_error/\",\n      \"title\": \"Unraveling the Mystery of WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR: Causes ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-12-19\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to content\\n\\n[TheTechyLife](https://thetechylife.com/)\\n\\n[Home](https://thetechylife.com) » [Tech Tips](https://thetechylife.com/tech-tips/) » Unraveling the Mystery of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR: Causes, Symptoms, and Solutions\\n\\n# Unraveling the Mystery of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR: Causes, Symptoms, and Solutions\\n\\nDecember 19, 2025 by [John Elmore](https://thetechylife.com/author/john/ \\\"View all posts by John Elmore\\\")\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a type of Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) error that occurs when a hardware error is detected, and the system is unable to recover from it. This error can be caused by a variety of factors, including hardware failures, driver issues, and system configuration problems. In this article, we will delve into the causes, symptoms, and solutions of the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, providing readers with a comprehensive understanding of this complex issue.\\n\\n## Understanding WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a critical error that occurs when the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA) detects an uncorrectable hardware error. WHEA is a framework that allows the operating system to detect and handle hardware errors, such as memory errors, CPU errors, and other hardware failures. When an uncorrectable error is detected, the system will typically display a blue screen with an error message, indicating that the system has encountered a critical failure.\\n\\n### Causes Of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nThere are several causes of the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, including:\\n\\nOverheating of the system, which can cause hardware components to fail or malfunction. **Inspecting the cooling system and ensuring proper airflow** can help prevent overheating.  \\nFaulty or failing hardware components, such as RAM, CPU, or motherboard. **Running diagnostic tests** can help identify faulty hardware.  \\nDriver issues, such as outdated or corrupted drivers.\\n**Updating drivers to the latest version** can help resolve driver-related issues.  \\nSystem configuration problems, such as incorrect BIOS settings or conflicting hardware. **Checking the BIOS settings and ensuring that all hardware components are compatible** can help resolve system configuration issues.  \\nPower supply issues, such as a failing power supply or inadequate power delivery. **Checking the power supply and ensuring that it is sufficient for the system** can help prevent power-related issues.\\n\\n### Symptoms Of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nThe symptoms of the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR can vary, but common symptoms include:\\n\\nA blue screen with an error message indicating that the system has encountered a critical failure.  \\nThe system crashing or freezing, often with no warning.  \\nThe system restarting repeatedly, with no opportunity to save work or data.  \\nError messages indicating that the system has detected a hardware error or failure.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techlasi.com/pc/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-12\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [MK Usmaan](https://techlasi.com/author/mkusman22/ \\\"View all posts by MK Usmaan\\\") / February 12, 2026\\n\\nAre you facing the dreaded blue screen with a WHEA uncorrectable error message? You’re not alone. This frustrating hardware related error has troubled computer users for years, but with advances in diagnostic technology in 2026, we now have better solutions than ever before. This comprehensive guide will walk you through everything you need to know about WHEA errors, from understanding what they are to implementing the most effective fixes using the latest tools and techniques.\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\n## **What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) uncorrectable error occurs when Windows detects a serious hardware problem that it cannot recover from automatically.\\nUnlike correctable hardware errors that Windows can resolve on the fly, uncorrectable errors force your system to shut down to prevent potential damage to your hardware or data corruption.\\n\\n### **Windows Hardware Error Architecture**\\n\\nWindows Hardware Error Architecture is a platform level error handling mechanism introduced in [Windows Vista](https://techlasi.com/savvy/windows-vs-linux-vs-macos/) that provides a standardized way for the operating system to handle hardware errors. WHEA improves upon the older Machine Check Architecture by offering enhanced error reporting and more detailed diagnostic information.\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n  \\n    + Windows Hardware Error Architecture\\n    + Common Error Codes Associated with WHEA Errors\\n* Primary Causes of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n  \\n    + Hardware Component Failures\\n    + Overclocking Issues\\n    + Driver and Firmware Problems\\n* Symptoms and Identification of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n+ Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) Appearances\\n    + Event Viewer Diagnostics\\n* Step-by-Step Troubleshooting Guide\\n  \\n    + Immediate Actions to Take\\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Procedures\\n    + Hardware Component Verification\\n* Prevention Strategies for WHEA Errors\\n  \\n    + Proper System Maintenance\\n    + Cooling Solutions and Temperature Management\\n    + Safe Overclocking Practices\\n* Recent Developments in WHEA Error Management\\n  \\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Tools\\n    + AI Assisted Troubleshooting\\n* Conclusion\\n* FAQs\\n  \\n    + Can software cause WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + How can I tell which hardware component is causing my WHEA error?\\n    + Are WHEA errors covered under warranty?\\n    + Can updating BIOS fix WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + Why do WHEA errors sometimes occur only during specific activities like gaming?\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ninjaone.com/blog/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-in-windows-11\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix \\\"WHEA_Uncorrectable_Error\\\" in Windows 11 | NinjaOne\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"## Troubleshooting WHEA uncorrectable error code on Windows 11 persistence\\n\\nUse these checks to pinpoint why WHEA events continue after initial repairs.\\n\\n* **WHEA persists after update:** Test RAM and storage hardware to confirm components are not failing under load.\\n* **WHEA Uncorrectable Error occurs under heavy load:** CPU instability is likely in such cases. Remove overclock settings and retest.\\n* **WHEA uncorrectable error occurs during gaming:** Update GPU drivers and verify PCIe bus stability with stress or diagnostics tools.\\n* **Happens after sleep or resume:** Update chipset, power management, and storage firmware to address instability.\\n* **Frequent events with no clear device:** Motherboard voltage regulation issues might be present and require board-level diagnostics.\\n\\n## Restore stability by fixing the WHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error signals a hardware fault that Windows cannot recover from.\\nBy identifying the failing component, updating firmware, correcting overclock settings, and validating system behavior with diagnostics, most issues can be resolved without replacing the entire system.\\n\\n**Related topics:**\\n\\n* How to Update BIOS on Your Windows PC\\n* How to Detect and Analyze Blue Screens of Death (BSOD) with PowerShell\\n* IT Guide: How to Run BSOD Troubleshooter in Windows 10\\n* How to Debug Crash Dumps using WinDbg in Windows 10\\n* How to Enable or Disable BSOD Automatic Restart in Windows\\n\\nStart your Free Trial\\n\\nEmbracing Automation at Every Level\\n\\n## FAQs\\n\\n### What is the most common cause of WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nMost cases trace back to unstable CPU or memory behavior. This is often due to failing hardware, outdated firmware, or residual overclock settings. ### Why does the WHEA error only appear under heavy load?\\n\\nHigh load exposes marginal instability in the CPU, RAM, or PCIe bus. Stress tests help reproduce these conditions and confirm the failing component.\\n### Can storage devices cause WHEA errors?\\n\\nAbsolutely. Failing SSDs or NVMe controllers trigger WHEA events. SMART checks and vendor diagnostics can help detect or confirm storage faults. ### What if updating BIOS and resetting overclocks do not fix the issue?\\n\\nIn such cases, retest RAM and CPU behavior independently. Persistent WHEA events usually indicate a failing hardware piece that needs replacement. ### Can GPU drivers be responsible for WHEA errors?\\n\\nYes. PCIe signaling or GPU driver faults can present as WHEA errors during gaming or 3D workloads. Updating GPU drivers and checking PCIe stability will help isolate these cases.\\n\\n* Categories: IT Ops\\n\\nYou might also like\\n\\nBack to Blog Home\\n\\n### Try our #1 rated endpoint management software on G2\\n\\nFree Trial\\n\\nNo credit card required, full access to all features.\\n\\nWebinar\\n\\n### **NinjaOne 12.0 Feature Updates:** What You Need to Know\\n\\n[Register now](https://see.ninjaone.com/120webinarEN)\\n\\n### Automate the Hardest Parts of IT\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.positioniseverything.net/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"+ [CPU](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/hardware/cpu/)\\n  \\n    + [Outlook](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/microsoft-office/outlook/)\\n    + [Powerpoint](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/microsoft-office/powerpoint/)\\n\\nSearch for:\\n\\nCategory [Blog](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/blog/)\\n\\n# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [positioniseverything](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/) Published May 17, 2026 21 min read\\n\\n* Author\\n* Recent Posts\\n\\n[](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/ \\\"positioniseverything\\\")\\n\\n[positioniseverything](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/)\\n\\n[](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/ \\\"positioniseverything\\\")\\n\\nLatest posts by positioniseverything ( [see all](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/) )\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is one of the more serious Windows blue screen errors because it usually points to a low-level hardware, firmware, or driver problem rather than a simple app crash. It can appear during gaming, startup, heavy workloads, Windows updates, or even while the PC is idle, often with little warning beyond a sudden restart and a stop code.\\n\\nIn 2026, the safest way to handle this error is to diagnose it methodically: check temperatures and power stability, remove unstable overclocks, test RAM and storage, review CPU and GPU behavior, update drivers, and verify BIOS/UEFI settings before replacing parts. A careful approach helps separate a temporary configuration issue from signs of failing hardware.\\n\\n[Guide Helped? Tip Us](https://ko-fi.com/yorkermedia) ×\\n\\n|\\\\# |Preview |Product |Price | |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|1 |[Anker USB C Hub, 7in1 Multi-Port USB Adapter for Laptop/Mac, 4K@60Hz USB C to HDMI Splitter, 85W Max PD, 2 USB 3.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.securedatarecovery.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR BSOD Secure Data Recovery https://www.securedatarecovery.com › ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* Home\\n  \\n  >\\n* Blog\\n  \\n  >\\n* How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\n# How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR BSOD on Windows\\n\\nPosted by\\n\\nYevgeniy Reznik\\n\\nPublished:\\n\\nJun 20, 2025\\n\\nReviewed by\\n\\nUpdated:\\n\\nFeb 19, 2026\\n\\nmin. read\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\nGet the Latest News\\n\\nSign-up Success!\\n\\nPlease enter a valid email\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a specific type of blue screen of death (BSOD) that appears on Windows 10 and Windows 11 systems when the operating system detects a critical hardware issue. It’s triggered by the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA) — a built-in system that monitors for hardware problems and reports when a component, such as the CPU, GPU, RAM, or motherboard, encounters a failure it cannot recover from. While it can be unsettling to see your device crash unexpectedly, this stop code is designed to protect your system from further damage by halting operations safely.\\nIn most cases, the underlying cause of this error is related to hardware instability. This could mean overheating, misconfigured BIOS or UEFI settings, faulty device drivers, or hardware that’s beginning to show signs of wear. However, not all causes are strictly hardware-based. The error can also stem from critical system files and firmware-level software that manage how Windows interacts with your hardware. Corruption in these layers, or conflicts introduced by recent Windows updates, firmware changes, or overclocking, can all contribute to the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR.\\n\\nWhile some users are able to troubleshoot this issue successfully on their own, others may find that the error recurs or prevents normal startup. If valuable data is stored on the affected computer, it’s essential to proceed cautiously. Running stress tests or reinstalling Windows without a backup can sometimes make data recovery more difficult.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://umatechnology.org/how-to-find-the-cause-and-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How To Find The Cause And Fix Whea-Uncorrectable-Error - UMA Technology\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* **Operational continuity** : In enterprise environments, hardware errors can halt production, leading to costly downtime.\\n\\nRecent trends up to 2024 show an increase in hardware-based errors, especially as systems push hardware limits with overclocking, high-density RAM modules, and high-speed SSDs. Additionally, supply chain issues and manufacturing defects can contribute to hardware degradation. Proper diagnosis has become a key skill for system administrators and developers managing high-availability infrastructures.\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## Understanding the WHEA-UNCORRECTABLE-ERROR\\n\\n### What Is WHEA and How Does it Work?\\n\\nThe **Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA)** is a built-in component of Windows that detects, reports, and logs hardware errors. It works closely with CPU features like **Machine Check Architecture (MCA)** , supported by Intel and AMD processors, to monitor hardware health in real time.\\nWhen a hardware fault occurs, WHEA captures detailed information—error type, severity, and affected components—and records it into the Windows Event Log. If the error is severe enough to jeopardize system stability, Windows initiates a BSOD with the message:\\n\\n> **WHEA-USD-UNCORRECTABLE-ERROR**\\n> \\n> \\n\\nThis indicates an uncorrectable hardware error detected by the system that cannot be remedied through error correction mechanisms.\\n\\n### Types of Hardware Errors Leading to WHEA-UNCORRECTABLE-ERROR\\n\\nCommon causes include:\\n\\n* **Memory (RAM) Failures** : Faulty or mismatched RAM modules, corrupted data, or overheating memory chips.\\n* **CPU Faults or Overheating** : Defective processors, overheating due to inadequate cooling, or overclocking.\\n* **Motherboard/Chipset Defects** : Faulty PCIe slots, VRMs (Voltage Regulator Modules), or BIOS/UEFI issues.\\n* **Power Supply Issues** : Voltage surges, insufficient power delivering unstable voltages.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://couldask.com/en/guides/tech/oswindows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11 — Step-by-Step Guide\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-27\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Sunday, June 28\\n\\nTheme\\n\\nEN ▾\\n\\n[Русский](https://couldask.com/ru/kak-ispravit-oshibku-whea-uncorrectable-error) [English](https://couldask.com/en/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error)\\n\\n🏠 Home Sections: All 📖 Guides 🔧 Fixes 💡 Concepts ⚖️ Compare 🛠️ Tools Справка\\n\\n×\\n\\n#### Help\\n\\nUse the search bar to find error codes or manuals. Articles are categorized in the top menu.\\n\\nSubcategories: Back All Adults Contact Excel Git Google Mail Media Windows More 7 ▾\\n\\n### Select Subcategory\\n\\n×\\n\\nHome / Guides / IT & Tech / Windows\\n\\nIT & Tech\\n\\n# How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11\\n\\nCouldAsk Editorial 27\\\\.06.2026 2 min 👁️ 139\\n\\nQuick Solution\\n\\nError 0x00000124 is a critical hardware failure (overheating, overclocking, or power issues). Key steps: reset BIOS to factory defaults, disable overclocking, and check system files and disk integrity.\\nBlue screen of death with WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR and stop code 0x00000124 on a computer monitor The **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** (stop code `0x00000124` ) is a critical failure of the Windows Hardware Error Architecture. Unlike many other Blue Screen of Death (BSoD) errors, this one indicates a hardware issue in 90% of cases, rather than a software glitch.\\n\\n## Main Causes of the Error\\n\\nThe system protects itself to prevent physical damage to the components. The primary culprits are:\\n\\n* Overheating of the processor (CPU) or graphics card (GPU).\\n* Unstable overclocking or enabled XMP profiles for RAM.\\n* A faulty power supply unit (PSU) causing voltage spikes.\\n* Physical wear and tear of the system drive (SSD/HDD).\\n\\n## Step-by-Step Solution\\n\\n### Step 1: Disable Overclocking\\n\\nIf you have overclocked your CPU or RAM, revert to the base settings.\\n1\\\\. Restart your computer and enter the BIOS/UEFI (usually by pressing `Del` or `F2` ).\\n2\\\\.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4353d96ffeDX0dEXoc77qyHt\"\n}",
