      "timestamp": 1783146287570
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "websearch",
      "code": "{\"query\": \"iFixit repairability score methodology hardware errors\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_1bf8d3202acb491295bc751d6587325b\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.techbloat.com/ifixit-gives-fairphone-5-perfect-repairability-score.html\",\n      \"title\": \"iFixit Gives Fairphone 5 Perfect Repairability Score\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-26\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"This makes common repairs far less intimidating for people who would normally assume a broken phone means a replacement phone.\\n\\nThe most visible example is the removable battery. On many modern smartphones, battery replacement requires softening glue, removing fragile display assemblies, and navigating tightly packed cables. On the Fairphone 5, the back cover can be removed and the battery can be swapped directly. Since lithium-ion batteries naturally degrade after years of charging, this single design choice can extend the usable life of the phone by a significant margin.\\n\\n### Parts designed for straightforward replacement\\n\\n* **Battery:** removable without specialist equipment, making long-term ownership more practical.\\n* **Display:** replaceable with screws and connectors rather than aggressive glue, reducing the risk of damage during repair.\\n* **USB-C port:** separated into its own module, so charging issues do not require replacing the entire main board.\\n* **Cameras:** modular camera units can be removed and replaced if damaged or if a supported upgrade becomes available.\\n* **Speakers and earpiece:** accessible as individual components rather than being permanently bonded into the chassis.\\n* **Back cover:** removable and replaceable, helping the phone survive drops and cosmetic wear.\\n\\nThis modularity matters because it targets the failures that usually push consumers toward premature upgrades. A cracked screen, weak battery, damaged charging port, or faulty speaker can make a phone feel obsolete even when the processor, memory, and software remain perfectly usable. By turning these failures into manageable repairs, Fairphone changes the economics of ownership. The cost and inconvenience of maintenance become closer to replacing a laptop component than buying a new sealed device.\\n\\nFairphone also supports this design with spare parts availability and repair information.\\nA modular phone is only useful if replacement components can actually be purchased, and the Fairphone approach treats parts as part of the product ecosystem rather than an afterthought. For consumers, that means more control over the device after purchase. For independent repair shops, it reduces guesswork and lowers the chance of damaging glued or serialized components during service.\\n\\nThe design does involve trade-offs. A modular phone can be slightly thicker than some premium flagships, and Fairphone prioritizes longevity and serviceability over the thinnest possible chassis or the most tightly integrated internal layout. But those choices are deliberate. The Fairphone 5 shows that a modern smartphone can still offer high-end features while giving users practical access to the components that determine how long the device remains useful.\\n\\n##### Rank #3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/repairability\",\n      \"title\": \"Repairability iFixit · https://www.ifixit.com › repairability\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Repairable Products Make Good Sense\\n\\n# **Repair is good for people, the planet, and product longevity** .\\n\\n# We rate products to make it easier to buy repairable devices.\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartphone-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Smartphones\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartphone-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/tablet-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Tablets\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/tablet-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Laptops\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-earbud-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Wireless Earbuds\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-earbud-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/e-reader-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# E-readers\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.\\ncom/repairability/e-reader-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartwatch-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Smartwatches\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartwatch-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/mini-pc-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Mini PCs\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/mini-pc-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/handheld-game-console-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Handheld Game Consoles\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/handheld-game-console-repairability-scores)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-headphones-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# Wireless Headphones\\n\\n[View Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/wireless-headphones-repairability-scores)\\n\\n# What is Repairability?\\n\\nRepairability means making it possible—and ideally easy—to repair a product.\\nA repairable product is designed with disassembly in mind (it should be easy to take apart and put back together). It must also have parts, tools, service documentation, and software available, as well as no artificial barriers to repair such as parts pairing. Together, these aspects make up the repair ecosystem.\\n\\n[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/gold-standard)\\n\\n# Repairable Products Make a Difference\\n\\n# 80% choose repairable\\n\\nFrance now requires that electronics manufacturers put a repairability score at the point of sale. The vast majority of French consumers say they [would give up their favorite brand](https://news.samsung.com/fr/sondage-indice-reparabilite) for a more repairable one.\\n\\n# 92% less waste\\n\\n[Microsoft found](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.dropbox.com/s/0s1i1m6efee7cbu/Summary%2520of%2520Sustainability%2520Benefits%2520of%2520Microsoft%2520Device%2520Repair.pdf?\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/smartphone-repairability-scores\",\n      \"title\": \"Smartphone Repairability Scores | Most Repairable Phones - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-30\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Smartphone Repairability Scores\\n\\nJump to Scores\\n\\n# You have the right to repair the things you own—but how easily can that be done?\\n\\nTo find out, our engineers tear down the latest smartphones and score their repairability from zero (unrepairable) to ten (easiest to repair) so you can pick a product that is easy to repair and lasts as long as possible.\\n\\n# What makes a repairable device?\\n\\nIt should be straightforward to disassemble and replace whatever’s broken, using parts and instructions supplied (or endorsed) by the manufacturer. But that’s just to start—repairability means so much more. For full details, see our [repairability scoring explainer](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability) .\\n\\n# Repairability is a moving target\\n\\nWe update our scoring rubric frequently to stay current with new technologies, materials, and design trends.\\nThis means that devices scored in years past might not fare exactly the same if they were re-scored today, but they can be readily compared with their contemporaries. For a precise list of criteria used to calculate each score, click the scorecard version number linked to each device below. For a downloadable (CSV) list of all scores, [click here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1R_egXm7iwR0isCt_UxcGtheFEwLj9SNhxC5DWnAqKIc/edit=0) .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# Smartphone Scores\\n\\nSorted by newest to oldest\\n\\n# iPhone Air\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/iPhone_Air)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Great design prioritizes screen repairs while giving access to all other parts through the back glass.\\n* Clever electrically-releasing adhesive streamlines battery replacements.\\n* Repair parts and instructions are available straight from Apple.\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n* Four different screwhead types and the continued reliance on adhesives complicate basic repairs.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.\\ncom/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/News/113171/iphone-air-teardown)**\\n\\n# iPhone 17 Pro\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/iPhone_17_Pro)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Display and battery repairs are well-prioritized, though not as well as in other (dual-entry) iPhone models.\\n* Torx screws secure the battery assembly in place, making replacements straightforward.\\n* Repair parts and instructions are available straight from Apple.\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n* Five different screwhead types and the continued reliance on adhesives complicate basic repairs.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/News/113388/iphone-17-pro-teardown)**\\n\\n# Google Pixel 10\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Google_Pixel_10)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Screen repairs are prioritized, and all other parts are under the back glass—which doesn’t require heat to remove.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability\",\n      \"title\": \"How Is the iFixit Repairability Score Calculated?\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Free Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\nHow iFixit Scores Repairability\\n\\nProduct Design\\n\\n# How iFixit Scores Repairability\\n\\n## What's a repairability score, and how is that calculated?\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/User/668072/Jeff+Suovanen)\\n\\nArticle by: [Jeff Suovanen](https://www.ifixit.com/User/668072/Jeff+Suovanen) [@jeffsu](https://www.ifixit.com/User/668072/Jeff+Suovanen)\\n\\n* May 18, 2023\\n* Filed under: Repairability , Product Design\\n* Comments\\n\\nShare\\n\\nEveryone wants their favorite phone or laptop to get an awesome repairability score. So do we! Unfortunately, we don’t make the rules.\\n\\nWait a minute—we do make the rules! At iFixit we’ve been wrenching on gadgets of all kinds for two decades, so we’ve developed strong opinions about what makes something easy to fix, or not. The iFixit repairability score, first introduced all the way back in 2011, is a reflection of those values.\\nWe’ve often hinted at all the things that make or break a repairability score—modular components good, reliance on adhesives bad, etc.—but as keen observers have noted, it’s a long and winding trans-dimensional hyperspace service tunnel from there to actual hard numbers on the iFixit scorecard.\\n\\nWell, strap in and hold onto your propeller cap, because today we’re going all the way down the tunnel. Let’s explore how iFixit repairability scoring actually works.\\n\\n## What Does “Repairable” Mean?\\n\\nCritical Components: _How sad are you if this breaks?_ and, _How often does this break?_ (PS: Search your feelings—you know this device)\\n\\nBefore we can score anything, we have to define it. Under our working definition, a highly repairable device:\\n\\n1. Is straightforward to disassemble and reassemble, nondestructively and reversibly\\n2. Requires only inexpensive, widely available tools for common fixes, and\\n3.\\nGives priority access to critical components—those most crucial to device function and/or most likely to require service.\\n\\nThose three things can get you pretty far on your way to a successful repair. But most people also need **instructions** and access to **replacement parts** . These last two things help complete the repair _ecosystem_ —the environment needed for repairs to survive and thrive. Ideally, they’d be provided by the original equipment manufacturer (OEM).\\n\\nBut creating a robust repair ecosystem is easier said than done. iFixit arose because over the years, many OEMs struggled (or even refused) to provide the instructions and parts customers needed to keep their stuff working. So we figured out how to do it without them, or even for them, as often as possible. (Happily, we’re now regularly [teaming up](https://www.ifixit.com/collaborations) .)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techrt.com/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics/\",\n      \"title\": \"Smartphone Repairability Score Statistics 2026: Best Models for Long-Term Value • TechRT\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-19\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[TechRT Logo](https://techrt.com/)\\n\\n[TechRT](https://techrt.com/)\\n\\nTechnology, Real Time\\n\\nSearch\\n\\n[TechRT Logo](https://techrt.com/)\\n\\n[Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://techrt.com/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics/&display=popup&ref=plugin&src=share_button \\\"Share on Facebook\\\") [Tweet](https://twitter.com/share?url=https://techrt.com/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics/&text=Smartphone%20Repairability%20Score%20Statistics%202026%3A%20Best%20Models%20for%20Long-Term%20Value \\\"Share on Twitter\\\") [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https://techrt.com/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics/ \\\"Share on LinkedIn\\\") [Pin](https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://techrt.com/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics/&media=https://techrt.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics.\\njpg&description=Smartphone%20Repairability%20Score%20Statistics%202026:%20Best%20Models%20for%20Long-Term%20Value \\\"Share on Pinterest\\\")\\n\\n[Smartphone Ownership Lifecycle Statistics Up Next ### Smartphone Ownership Lifecycle Statistics 2026: Surprising Truth About Phone Lifespan](https://techrt.com/smartphone-ownership-lifecycle-statistics/)\\n\\n[Smartphone Repairability Score Statistics](https://techrt.com/smartphone-repairability-score-statistics/)\\n\\n[TechRT](https://techrt.com) / [Technology](https://techrt.com/topics/technology/)\\n\\n# Smartphone Repairability Score Statistics 2026: Best Models for Long-Term Value\\n\\nAvatar of Tushar Thakur [Tushar Thakur](https://techrt.com/about/team/tushar-thakur/)\\n\\nLast updated on: February 19, 2026\\n\\n[Smartphone](https://techrt.com/smartphone-statistics/) repairability has moved from a niche concern to a mainstream metric.\\nWith consumers holding devices longer and repair-friendly policies emerging in major markets, ease of repair now influences purchase decisions and sustainability outcomes. Both industry regulators and independent teardown labs are shaping how manufacturers design devices, while consumers save money by fixing rather than replacing hardware. In sectors from wireless carriers to enterprise device fleets, _repairability scores_ are now a factor in procurement and lifecycle planning. Scroll on to explore the latest repair rankings, trends, and what they mean for users and the environment.\\n\\n## Editor’s Choice\\n\\n* **Fairphone 6 scored a perfect 10/10 repairability** , topping independent teardown charts for 2025 and 2026.\\n* Most flagship smartphones still average between **5–7/10 on repairability** by industry teardown standards.\\n* iFixit teardowns show repairability scores range **from 0 to 10** across modern phones.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.0\",\n      \"title\": \"Repairability Scoring Rubric v2.0 - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* Edit\\n* Options\\n\\n* History\\n\\n# Repairability Scoring Rubric v2.0\\n\\nHere you'll find a summary of the various criteria iFixit considers when calculating repairability scores under scorecard version 2.0.\\n\\n**Scoring Factors**\\n\\n| |Weight |Note |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n|Design for Repair |80% |_Ease of disassembly/reassembly_ |\\n|Service Manual (if any) |10% |_Free, public, complete, available via OEM support site_ |\\n|Parts Availability & Cost |10% |_Only OEM parts considered_ |\\n|Unique Product Identifier |N/A |_Gating function for full credit on service manual, parts availability_ |\\n|Parts Pairing |N/A |_Penalty only, global, up to -100%_ |\\n\\n**Factors Not Considered**\\n\\n|Software Updates |_Duration of software security updates is slated for inclusion in a future version of the scorecard._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Other |_[Reserved]_ |\\n\\n**Revisions from v1.9**\\n\\n|Tools and Scaling Factors |_Added new tools and adjusted tool categorizations and scaling factors._ |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Proxy Times |_Removed/replaced deprecated actions and prioritized actions and proxy times associated with specific hardware design features._ |\\n|Scoring Definitions and Guidance |_Refined internal definitions and guidance for numerous scoring criteria for greater consistency and ease of use._ |\\n\\n**Summary of Revisions**\\n\\nBlock Image\\n\\n**Reference**\\n\\n* [How iFixit Scores Repairability](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability)\\n* Provisional Scoring Explained\\n* [Smartphone Repairability Index](https://www.ifixit.com/smartphone-repairability)\\n\\n### Author\\n\\n#### Jeff Suovanen\\n\\nMember since: 08/06/13\\n\\n453,031 Reputation\\n\\n259 Guides authored\\n\\nBadges: 49\\n\\n* \\n* \\n* \\n\\n\\\\+46 more badges\\n\\n### Team\\n\\n#### iFixit Member of iFixit\\n\\nStaff\\n\\n122 Members\\n\\n26,483 Guides authored\\n\\n### 1 Comment\\n\\nAdd Comment\\n\\nSlaqe diwr fksjawo f\\n\\nsalad11223300@gmail.com \\\\- Mar 5, 2026 Reply Share\\n\\n#### Add Comment\\n\\nCancel Post comment\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 9\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 47\\nPast 30 Days: 188\\n\\nAll Time: 3,645\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://winbuzzer.com/2024/06/24/microsoft-surface-devices-receive-praise-for-repairability-xcxwbn\",\n      \"title\": \"iFixit Praises Surface Pro 11 and Surface Laptop 7 Repairability with High 8/10 Score\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-11-07\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# iFixit Praises Surface Pro 11 and Surface Laptop 7 Repairability with High 8/10 Score\\n\\nAccording to iFixit, the Surface line of devices have performed \\\"a stunning and swift U-turn from unrepairable to very repairable\\\".\\n\\n[Markus Kasanmascheff](https://winbuzzer.com/author/markus/ \\\"Markus Kasanmascheff\\\")\\n\\nBy [Markus Kasanmascheff](https://winbuzzer.com/author/markus/)\\n\\nJune 24, 2024 9:45 pm CEST\\n\\nMicrosoft Surface Pro 11 Copilot Plus official\\n\\niFixit has awarded the [Surface Pro 11](https://winbuzzer.com/2024/05/20/microsoft-introduces-surface-pro-with-ai-powered-upgrades-xcxwbn/) and [Surface Laptop 7](https://winbuzzer.com/2024/05/21/microsoft-launches-surface-laptop-with-snapdragon-x-processors-2-xcxwbn/) high repairability ratings, scoring 8 out of 10. This is a dramatic improvement compared to the first Surface Laptop, which was notoriously challenging to repair and received a score of 0 from the repair experts.\\niFixit is an American e-commerce and how-to website that sells repair parts and publishes free online repair guides for consumer electronics and gadgets that have gained high popularity online.\\n\\n## **Streamlined Disassembly in New Surface Lineup**\\n\\nAccording to iFixit, _“the Surface Laptop 7 is an astonishingly repair friendly device, almost the antithesis of the original Surface Laptop”_ .\\n\\nMicrosoft’s hardware team has been pushing for improved repairability over the past several years. The [Surface Laptop 7](https://winbuzzer.com/2024/05/21/microsoft-launches-surface-laptop-with-snapdragon-x-processors-2-xcxwbn/) , inspired by the Framework 13’s user-friendly design, made its service manuals available simultaneously with the device’s release—a rare industry move.\\n\\nThe [Surface Pro 11](https://winbuzzer.com/2024/05/20/microsoft-introduces-surface-pro-with-ai-powered-upgrades-xcxwbn/) features QR codes and Wayfinder markers to assist users during disassembly.\\nTo access its battery, the Surflink cable and thermal system must first be removed. Non-magnetic screws securing the Surflink port add ease to reassembly tasks.\\n\\niFixit praises how straightforward it is to replace the Surface Laptop 7’s fan, comparing it to the MSI GS65, where fan access requires removing the motherboard and entire cooling system. This marks a noteworthy enhancement in Microsoft’s approach to making their products more repairable.\\n\\n_“A special mention should be made of how most components are accessible without the need to remove additional layers. Need to replace the battery? No problem, it’s just a few screws and a bracket. What if you need to clean the fan? Easy. Just peel back the Surflink cable and undo three screws.”_\\n\\nFor the [Surface Laptop 7](https://winbuzzer.com/2024/05/21/microsoft-launches-surface-laptop-with-snapdragon-x-processors-2-xcxwbn/) , Microsoft has designed a simpler disass\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores\",\n      \"title\": \"Laptop Repairability Scores | Most Repairable Laptops - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-07-03\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Laptop Repairability Scores\\n\\nJump to Scores\\n\\n# You have the right to repair the things you own—but how easily can that be done?\\n\\nTo find out, our engineers tear down the latest laptops and score their repairability from zero (unrepairable) to ten (easiest to repair) so you can pick a product that is easy to repair and lasts as long as possible.\\n\\n# What makes a repairable device?\\n\\nIt should be straightforward to disassemble and replace whatever’s broken, using parts and instructions supplied (or endorsed) by the manufacturer. But that’s just to start—repairability means so much more. For full details, see our [repairability scoring explainer](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability) .\\n\\n# Repairability is a moving target\\n\\nWe update our scoring rubric frequently to stay current with new technologies, materials, and design trends.\\nThis means that devices scored in years past might not fare exactly the same if they were re-scored today, but they can be readily compared with their contemporaries. For a precise list of criteria used to calculate each score, click the scorecard version number linked to each device below. For a downloadable (CSV) list of all scores, [click here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1R_egXm7iwR0isCt_UxcGtheFEwLj9SNhxC5DWnAqKIc/edit=0) .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# Laptop Scores\\n\\nSorted by newest to oldest\\n\\n# Lenovo ThinkPad T14 Gen 7 and T16 Gen 5\\n\\n2026\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Storage and memory are readily repairable/upgradeable using industry-standard parts.\\n* The battery is easily replaced, and the keyboard replacement procedure is best-in-class.\\n* Overall very high modularity, including individually replaceable Thunderbolt ports.\\n* Lenovo provides thorough repair instructions and sells replacement parts.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)\\n\\n...\\n\\nifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.3)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/News/54122/macbook-pro-2021-teardown)**\\n\\n[View Legacy Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/legacy-laptop-scores)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.techspot.com/news/112991-ifixit-creating-repairability-scoring-standard-us-electronics.html\",\n      \"title\": \"iFixit is creating a repairability scoring standard for US electronics | TechSpot\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-07-03\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* \\n* \\n* \\n\\n* Trending\\n  \\n    + AI\\n    + Best CPUs\\n    + How Much RAM\\n    + DLSS 5\\n    + Google Chrome\\n    + CPU Benchmarking\\n    + Most Anticipated Games\\n* Reviews\\n  \\n    + Outstanding\\n    + CPU\\n    + Graphics Cards\\n    + Monitors\\n    + PC Buying Guide\\n    + Software\\n    + Gaming Benchmarks\\n* Features\\n  \\n    + Tech Culture\\n    + Must Reads\\n    + Legends of Tech\\n    + Explainers\\n    + Hardware\\n    + Gaming\\n* Downloads\\n  \\n    + Software Essentials\\n    + Popular Apps\\n    + Chrome\\n    + VMWare\\n    + Minecraft\\n    + Device Drivers\\n    + PS3 Firmware\\n* The Best\\n  \\n    + Best GPUs\\n    + Best Gaming Monitors\\n    + Best Monitors\\n    + Best SSD\\n    + Best Tablets\\n    + Best Mouse\\n    + Best PC Games\\n* Tech DB\\n  \\n    + CPU Database\\n    + Top Multi-core CPUs\\n    + Fastest Gaming CPUs\\n    + GPU Database\\n    + Fastest GPUs\\n* Product Finder\\n  \\n  Search\\n* Forums\\n  \\n    + Join TechSpot Elite\\n    + New Forum Posts\\n\\n* [Electronics](https://www.techspot.com/category/electronics/)\\n* [Industry](https://www.\\ntechspot.com/category/industry/)\\n* ifixit\\n* right to repair\\n\\n# iFixit is creating a repairability scoring standard for US electronics\\n\\n## A voluntary standard could give shoppers and lawmakers a clearer way to judge how fixable a device really is\\n\\n_By [Rob Thubron](https://www.techspot.com/community/staff/midian182.370608/) July 3, 2026, 8:14_\\n\\n[](https://www.techspot.com/images2/news/bigimage/2026/07/2026-07-03-image-6.jpg)\\n\\nServing tech enthusiasts for over 25 years.  \\nTechSpot means tech analysis and advice [you can trust](https://www.techspot.com/ethics.html) .\\n\\n**Why it matters:** iFixit is working with NSF to create a voluntary repairability scoring standard for electronics in the US. The aim is to give retailers, lawmakers, manufacturers, and consumers a clearer way to judge how easy a product is to repair before it is bought.\\n\\nThe repair specialist says the [new system](https://www.ifixit.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/16/macbook-neo-ifixit-most-repairable-macbook-in-years-battery-replacement\",\n      \"title\": \"The MacBook Neo is ‘the most repairable MacBook’ in years, according to iFixit | TechCrunch\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-03-16\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"young woman seated at a classroom desk using a MacBook Neo **Image Credits:** Apple\\n\\n[Hardware](https://techcrunch.com/category/hardware/)\\n\\n[](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2026%2F03%2F16%2Fmacbook-neo-ifixit-most-repairable-macbook-in-years-battery-replacement%2F) [](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2026%2F03%2F16%2Fmacbook-neo-ifixit-most-repairable-macbook-in-years-battery-replacement%2F&text=The+MacBook+Neo+is+%E2%80%98the+most+repairable+MacBook%E2%80%99+in+years%2C+according+to+iFixit&via=techcrunch) [](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.\\n\\n...\\n\\nMany of the new MacBook parts, including memory cards and battery, were glued down; iFixit gave that model a [1 out of 10 score](https://www.wired.com/2012/06/opinion-apple-retina-displa/) for repairability.\\n\\nSince then, Apple has faced criticism for [opposing some right to repair laws](https://www.404media.co/apple-is-lobbying-against-right-to-repair-again/) in states and creating so-called [parts pairing](https://www.ifixit.com/News/69320/how-parts-pairing-kills-independent-repair) barriers that limited or stopped devices from working with non-manufacturer parts. Laws allowing people to repair devices in states including Oregon then pushed the company [to lift restrictions](https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/11/technology/apple-iphone-repairs-parts.html) on repairing iPhones using older parts.\\n\\nMemory and storage are still soldered in the new MacBook Neo, making it hard to upgrade.\\n“But the parts that fail first are easier to reach than they have been on any MacBook in a long time,” iFixit said. “The battery is screwed down instead of glued in. The ports are modular. The display is easier to replace. The internal layout is unusually sensible.”\\n\\nTopics\\n\\n[Apple](https://techcrunch.com/tag/apple/) , [Hardware](https://techcrunch.com/category/hardware/) , [ifixit](https://techcrunch.com/tag/ifixit/) , [macbook neo](https://techcrunch.com/tag/macbook-neo/)\\n\\n_When you purchase through links in our articles, [we may earn a small commission](https://techcrunch.com/techcrunch-affiliate-monetization-standards/) . This doesn’t affect our editorial independence._\\n\\n[](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2026%2F03%2F16%2Fmacbook-neo-ifixit-most-repairable-macbook-in-years-battery-replacement%2F) [](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4353d96ffeDX0dEXoc77qyHt\"\n}",
